Install or update portslackware
    # portslackware -v <slackware-version>

  for version 13.37:
    # portslackware -v 13.37
  for version 13.1:
    # portslackware -v 13.1
  for version 12.2:
    # portslackware -v 12.2
  for auto-detect your version
    # portslackware

Create portslackware_database
    # portslackware -c

Install portslackware_database with package
    # portslackware -d portslackware_database-*_*.tar.bz2

Install portslackware_database with script
    # portslackware -s portslackware_database.sh

Help
    # portslackware -h

The default directory portslackware
    /usr/portslackware/

Install an application by scripts generated by portslackware
    /usr/portslackware/<class>/<application>/portscript.sh <Parameter>

More information about the portscript.sh
    # /usr/portslackware/<class>/<application>/portscript.sh -h

Editing the database
  default directory database /var/portslackware_database/

  Edit the file dependencies by putting <class>/<program>
  example:
    The program "gparted" needs the library "gtkmm" which is part of the class "libraries"
    # echo 'libraries/gtkmm' >> /var/portslackware_database/system/gparted/dependencies